==Constituent Schools== * School of Aerospace, Mechanical and Mechatronic Engineering * School of Chemical and Biomolecular Engineering * School of Civil Engineering * School of Electrical and Information Engineering * School of Information Technology * Graduate School of Engineering and IT
==Research Centres== * Warren Centre * ACIIC * AGSEI * Chemical Engineering Foundation * Australian Centre of Advanced Risk and Reliability Engineering * Electrical Engineering Foundation * The Civil and Mining Engineering Foundation * Centre for Geotechnical Research * Centre for Advanced Structural Engineering * Mechanical Engineering Foundation * Centre for Advanced Materials Technology * Cooperative Research Centre in Aerospace Structures
==Notable Alumni== * [[John Bradfield (engineer)|John Bradfield]] - designer of Sydney Harbour Bridge * Paul Scully-Power - Australia's first Astronaut * Michael Hintze - billionaire hedge fund manager and philanthropist * David Higgins - CEO of Network Rail and former CEO of Lend Lease * John Grills - billionaire founder of WorleyParsons
